JOHANNESBURG - Sassa wants another extension of its contract with Cash Paymaster Services. It’s asking the Constitutional Court to extend the contract by six months. READ: Sassa debacle: Post Office can't produce all cards Sassa says this will give the Post Office enough time to take over social grant payments. In 2017, the Constitutional Court granted Sassa a 12-month extension, allowing the agency time to find an alternative to CPS. That deadline expires at the end of March. eNCA